snippet.textDisplay: None of the reviews I've seen of this film have mentioned that Judy Dench was cast in the original Broadway performance of Cats as the lead. So this was no doubt a sentimental connection for her to return to it (now as a different character). Basically though, this project was a group of filmmakers vastly overestimating the power of motion capture and failing to understand that 90% of the charm of Cats comes from being a stage production. It just doesn't work as a film, even if the special effects weren't an uncanny valley nightmare.
snippet.textOriginal: None of the reviews I've seen of this film have mentioned that Judy Dench was cast in the original Broadway performance of _Cats_ as the lead.
